snippet.textDisplay:
This song has been a therapy for me since it was released.
All the people who think and say that this is not good enough, it is boring, could have been better etc - I truly truly pray to Allah that I wish you guys never get to connect with the depression that this song addresses. It is a dark dark place, but then, as we have been told, there's always light at the end of the tunnel. Even if it is dark today, it may or may not get better with time but you will be okay. You will find happiness anyway. Insha Allah.

snippet.textDisplay: Am I depressed!?!  I relate so much to Hannan's lyrics ... all I know is that I inch toward self awareness, self realization and self actualization all the time as a journey in my life.  My resume, under transferable skills, i also list "self care" too.  And to see my journey, especially related to career, represented on the screen is beyond words.  BTW Kaavish, their voice/sound is next level; plz produce more stuff.  Also, I loved the visual language of the song and the philosophy it created with the closure part cut out in the end: the shot where Hannan is looking ahead with his back in the frame as if preparing for the future -- keep on trucking, Hannan.  O Yaara moved me, emotionally.   Kudos Coke Studio.  Coke Studio Zindabad!
